ABUJA – The Progressives Project (TPP), the umbrella support group rooting for Vice President Yemi Osinbajo presidency in 2023 Wednesday in Abuja hosted representatives of over 500 support groups from across the country to a strategic meeting to stop the influence of moneybags at the forthcoming presidential primary of the APC. This is coming barely 48 hours after TPP committed a coalition of 57 youth and students’ groups, to lend support to the aspiration of Osinbajo to succeed President Mohammadu Buhari. At the TPP office in Abuja on Wednesday, former, serving and prospective candidates for councillorship, chairmanship, state and federal legislative positions, along with a few former and serving state commissioners exchanged views on how to achieve effective grassroots impact by selling the good qualities of Vice President Osinbajo and showcasing it as if the great value to the country than anticipated offers of monetary gifts by moneybags. 2023: Orji Uzor Kalu Wants Presidency Zoned To South-East NAF Special Forces Rescue Kidnap Victims Head of TPP’s Situation Room, Mr Jeffry Omoh, who addressed representatives of the support group drawn from the nation’s six geo-political zones emphasized that their strategy shall emphasize ‘mobilization of delegates’ patriotism, not mobilization of Naira’ Representatives were urged to “Go home, study their environment more, improve their interactions with people and return with suggestions and ideas that TPP and its constituent teams can work with”. “We thank all members of the approximately 500 support groups who are already identifying with us, with a firm commitment towards mobilising Nigeria towards achieving an Osinbajo Presidency in 2023,” he said. Dr Mustapha M. Jibril, Commissioner for Investment, Commerce and Industry in Niger state who spoke at occasion told the gathering that the loyalty demonstrated to President Muhammadu Buhari, disciplined focus and other good qualities of Professor Yemi Osinbajo remain a strong selling point for the Vice President adding that they work together to realize the overall objective. Speaking in a similar vein at the first interactive meeting of pro-Osinbajo groups, Mr Ibrahim Mohammed who drew attention to his family’s Kano origin stated that his family members have lived in Ibadan, Oyo state over the past one hundred and fifty years, adding that 2023 elections are not really going to be about zoning but about the prospects of unity, sustainable progress and development across all parts of the federation. POLL “Our efforts here and the motivation for supporting Osinbajo is not about whether political power goes north or south; it is about consolidating on what has been achieved in the past towards throttling into a better future for all under a trustworthy and very capable leadership that would not need to offer huge bribes to party delegates before its emergence,” he stated. Speaking in the same vein, Mr Precious Elekia from Cross River State said “It is time to vote for Nigeria and not a time to vote for Hausa, Igbo or Yoruba,” adding that Professor Yemi Osinbajo is a viable and sellable candidate that appeals to all dimensions of national interest.